    <briefdescription>
<para>Wrapper for strong type. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Strong types reinforce interfaces by making them more expressive, and less error-prone by forcing the right type. This is implemented by the following thin wrapper.</para>
<para>For example, In order to define a FrequencyKHz, uint16_t type:</para>
<para>enum class StKHz : uint32_t; // This just needs to be a unique. using KHz = <ref refid="structTTL__StrongType" kindref="compound">TTL_StrongType&lt;uint16_t, StKHz&gt;</ref>;</para>
<para>StrongTypes can be used in anywhere because to the outside world it looks exactly like the underlying type.</para>
<para>So a structure from the outside world can contain the follow when a KHz frequency is expected as a uint16_t;<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>struct ExternalData { KHz input_frequency_khz; }</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>would be 100% compability with the other unsafe code in the external entity that simple said</para>
<para>struct ExternalData { uint16_t input_frequency_khz; } </para>
    </detaileddescription>
